AIM

To calculate batting strike rate, bowling economy and evaluate the performance of a cricketer using Python conditional statements.

Algorithm
Start the program.
Take runs scored and number of balls faced as input.
Calculate strike rate using the formula: runs divided by balls multiplied by 100.
Check the batting performance using conditions and display the result.

Next take runs conceded, number of overs and wickets taken as input.
Calculate bowling economy by dividing runs conceded by overs.
Use conditions to determine whether the bowler is excellent, good or poor.

Then take number of catches as input.
If catches are greater than or equal to one, display active fielder.
Otherwise display needs improvement.
Stop the program.

SOURCE CODE

runs = int(input("Enter runs:"))
balls = int(input("Enter the number of balls faced:"))

strike_rate = runs/balls * 100

if runs > 50 and strike_rate > 120:
    print("Excellent Batter")
elif runs > 30 and strike_rate > 100:
    print("Good Batter")
elif runs > 20:
    print("Average Batter")
else:
    print("Poor Batter")

runs_conceded = int(input("Enter runs conceded:"))
overs = int(input("Enter overs:"))
wickets = int(input("Enter wickets taken:"))

economy = runs_conceded/overs

if wickets >= 3 and economy < 6:
    print("Excellent Bowler")
elif wickets >= 2 and economy < 8:
    print("Good Bowler")
else:
    print("Poor Bowler")

catches = int(input("Enter number of catches:"))

if catches >= 1:
    print("Active Fielder")
else:
    print("Needs Improvement")

